  <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>2 cups heavy cream</li>
    <li>1/4 cup powdered sugar</li>
    <li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li>
    <li>1 package graham crackers</li>
    <li>1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder</li>
    <li>1 cup chocolate chips (for the topping)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Instructions:</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>
      In a large bowl, whip the heavy cream with powdered sugar and vanilla
      extract until stiff peaks form.
    </li>
    <li>
      Line the bottom of a 9x13-inch baking dish with a layer of graham
      crackers.
    </li>
    <li>
      Spread a layer of whipped cream over the graham crackers, smoothing it out
      to cover evenly.
    </li>
    <li>
      Repeat layers, alternating graham crackers and whipped cream, until all
      the ingredients are used up. The top layer should be whipped cream.
    </li>
    <li>
      Refrigerate the cake for at least 4 hours, or preferably overnight, to let
      the flavors meld together.
    </li>
    <li>
      Once set, melt the chocolate chips in the microwave or using a double
      boiler. Drizzle the melted chocolate over the top of the cake.
    </li>
    <li>Serve chilled and enjoy this delicious, no-bake treat!</li>
  </ol>

